FBIS3-16830 "drsov054_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 National Affairs Crimean President Issues Decree on 27 March Poll LD1803212394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 18 Mar 94 LD1803212394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Crimea's President Yuriy Meshkov issued a decree today on organizing and holding a poll among Crimea's citizens on 27 March of this year, INTERFAX reported. Yuriy Meshkov approved the form for the poll. The document prescribes that Crimea's population will be polled on the following issues: -- On their attitude to dual citizenship; -- On the Crimeans' positions regarding the interrelation between Kiev and Simferopol on the basis of agreements and treaties; and also -- On granting Crimea's president the right to issue decrees that have force of law on issues that are not regulated by Crimean legislation. [passage omitted]
